            <title>[HBASE-5668] HRegionServer.checkFileSystem() should only abort() after fs is down for some time</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5668</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When checkFileSystem() fails then the region server should wait for sometime before aborting. By default, the timeout can be same as zookeeper session timeout.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When say a rack switch reboots or fails for a few minutes, and all the traffic to the region server dies ... then we don&apos;t want the region servers to unnecessarily kill themselves when ongoing compactions or flushes fail.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
